Abdomen.
Cerci with numerous bristles, with the smallest at the apex (
Fig. 7H
); shape conical, slightly curved, with apex straight and acuminate (
Fig. 7H
). Subgenital plate trapezoidal, with apex slightly convex (

Fig. 
7I

). Ovipositor slightly curved, with smooth margins (
